        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 6:57PM CST by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 655 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ganado, or 11 miles east of Edna, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bay City, El Campo, Wharton, Edna, Sweeny, Needville, Ganado, La
Ward, Pierce, Lolita, Markham, Van Vleck, Boling-Iago, southwestern
Wild Peach Village, Louise, Midfield, Lake Texana Dam, and Danevang.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CST for south central
and southeastern Texas.</instruction>
